              signatures. We then show how neural processes sum their energy in
              the local field potential in simulated and real-world recording
              scenarios. We find that the spectral power of neural processes is
              essentially determined by two aspects: 1) the distribution of
              neural events in time and 2) the waveform of the voltage induced
              by single neural events. Taken together, this work guides the
              interpretation of the Fourier spectrum of neural recordings and
              indicates that power increases in specific frequency bands do not
              necessarily reflect periodic neural activity. \#\#\# Competing
              Interest Statement The authors have declared no competing
